@startuml
' @id(SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE)
' @id(SEQ-DEPLOY-INSPECT)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-INSPECT)
'
' Objective-side runtime flow of the standalone /mdd-deploy utility
' skill and the additive /mdd-render rasterization of .mdd/deploy/**.
' The skill is guidance-only: it writes artifacts and a runbook and
' then STOPS. It never executes a deployment command.
'
' @desc(SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE, "How /mdd-deploy turns a one-line description into deployment guidance: validate the target is azure-container-apps, read MDD models + the target repo read-only, then STOP for a blocking clarification on ambiguity AND on any statically detectable go-live landmine (a generated config default contradicting what the shipped code supports, e.g. AOAI managed-identity vs an api-key-only server), write the deployment diagram, generate secure-by-default ../atlas-ate-server/infra/main.bicep (no store left more network-open than its peers — e.g. Key Vault Deny + bypass=AzureServices when Postgres/AOAI are private), write the runbook with a STOP before every state-changing/go-live step, enforce every atlas-ate-server invariant, then report and execute nothing.")
' @desc(SEQ-DEPLOY-INSPECT, "How /mdd-render (extended) rasterizes .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml to its deterministic .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg mirror so the deployment diagram is inspectable like every other diagram. Additive, non-gating.")
title /mdd-deploy guidance and inspection (objective)

actor "Operator" as Op
participant "/mdd-deploy\n(utility skill)" as Dep
participant ".mdd/models/\ncomponents + use-cases" as Models
participant "../atlas-ate-server\n(target repo, read-only)" as Target
database ".mdd/deploy/\nazure-container-apps/" as Store
participant "../atlas-ate-server/\ninfra/ (generated Bicep)" as Infra
participant "/mdd-render" as Render
database ".mdd/rendered/deploy/" as Rendered

== SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE ==
Op -> Dep : /mdd-deploy <deployment description>
alt target != azure-container-apps
  Dep --> Op : not yet supported (v1 = azure-container-apps only); stop
else target == azure-container-apps
  Dep -> Models : read components + use-cases (the "what")
  Dep -> Target : read README, Dockerfile, docker-compose.yml,\n.env.example, src (READ-ONLY)
  opt topology/security choice ambiguous OR a go-live landmine is statically detectable
    Dep -> Op : BLOCKING clarification (e.g. generated AOAI\nmanaged-identity default vs api-key-only server) —\nsame discipline as /mdd-cycle
    Op --> Dep : decision
    note right of Dep
      Mandatory blocking pause. The skill NEVER guesses an
      ambiguous decision, and NEVER demotes a detected
      go-live landmine to a buried runbook STOP note.
    end note
  end
  Dep -> Store : write diagram.puml (UML deployment diagram;\ndocumentation-only security stereotypes)
  Dep -> Infra : generate SECURE-BY-DEFAULT infra/main.bicep (+ modules):\nContainer Apps, ACR, Azure DB for PostgreSQL (TLS),\nKey Vault (Deny + bypass=AzureServices when peers private),\nsecret refs, ingress 8080, migration job
  Dep -> Store : write runbook.md (numbered steps; exact command,\nlocation, env/secret; STOP before every state-changing\nor go-live step incl. the billing production gate)
  note right of Dep
    Enforces every atlas-ate-server invariant:
    Key-Vault-only secrets, App Attest required,
    billing production multi-factor gate, BYOK
    never touches the server, DB TLS + at-rest,
    pre-traffic migration job, non-root, port 8080.
    Secure-by-default: no store left more network-open
    than its peers (auto-hardened, not deferred).
    Caveat: migrations-before-traffic stays procedural
    (documented v1 tradeoff, not auto-changed).
  end note
  Dep --> Op : report written files; review the diagram\nand run the runbook yourself. Executes NOTHING.
end

== SEQ-DEPLOY-INSPECT ==
Op -> Render : /mdd-render
Render -> Store : read .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml
Render -> Rendered : write .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg\n(deterministic mirror; additive, non-gating)
Render --> Op : rendered SVG list

note over Store
  .mdd/deploy/ is an inspection artifact only.
  /mdd-validate, /mdd-review and the /mdd-cycle
  parity loop never read it.
end note
@enduml
